	div#step-1.step.grid-container
		div.grid-50
			h2 Applications
			p In order to start using the Teech.io backend, the first thing you need to do is wiring up your application to your Teech.io backend. It's very simple, just add the application from your Teech.io dashboard. Each application has an ID that you need to use together with your API key in order to authenticate your application when requesting data from the backend.
			a(class="next-step-btn btn btn-primary btn-lg", data-href="#step-2") next <i class="fa fa-chevron-circle-right"></i>
		div.grid-50.walkthrough-example-image.walkthrough-1-step-image
	div#step-2.step.grid-container.set-hidden
		div.grid-50
			h2 API console
			p Through the API console you can manage all your collections and data: you can add, update, delete items within your collection and even query the collections.
			a(class="next-step-btn btn btn-primary btn-lg", data-href="#step-3") next <i class="fa fa-chevron-circle-right"></i>
		div.grid-50.walkthrough-example-image.walkthrough-2-step-image
	div#step-3.step.grid-container.set-hidden
		div.grid-50
			h2 Files browser
			p The files browser let you upload and manage the files that you need for your applications.
			a(class="next-step-btn btn btn-primary btn-lg", data-href="#step-4") next <i class="fa fa-chevron-circle-right"></i>
		div.grid-50.walkthrough-example-image.walkthrough-3-step-image
	div#step-4.step.grid-container.set-hidden
		div.grid-50
			h2 API
			p The REST API allows an app to interact with its backend on Teech.io programmatically via simple HTTP requests. The API is accessed via the http://api.teech.io domain.
			p JSON will be returned in all responses, including errors. The HTTP response codes are used to indicate the status of each request. 
			h4 Authentication
			p All requests to teech.io REST API require you to authenticate via HTTP headers. The <code>Teech-Application-Id</code> identifies the application you’re accessing and the <code>Teech-REST-API-key</code> authenticates your request.
			a(class="next-step-btn btn btn-primary btn-lg", data-href="#step-5") next <i class="fa fa-chevron-circle-right"></i>
		div.grid-50.walkthrough-example-image.walkthrough-4-step-image
	div#step-5.step.grid-container.set-hidden
		div.grid-50
			h2 Collections
			p Collections are grouping the objects within Teech.io backend. Collections are like tables in relational databases.
			p Next steps will give you an overview of how collections work and of the main collection types that you can use.
			a(class="next-step-btn btn btn-primary btn-lg", data-href="#step-6") next <i class="fa fa-chevron-circle-right"></i>
		div.grid-50.walkthrough-example-image.walkthrough-5-step-image
	div#step-6.step.grid-container.set-hidden
		div.grid-50
			h2 Key/Value
			p Key/Values pairs are the way you can define properties for each object stored in a collection.
			div.code-sample
				ul.nav.nav-tabs
					li.active: a(data-target="#http-get-sample", data-toggle="tab") GET
					li: a(data-target="#http-post-sample", data-toggle="tab") POST
					li: a(data-target="#http-put-sample", data-toggle="tab") PUT
					li: a(data-target="#http-delete-sample", data-toggle="tab") DELETE
				div.tab-content
					div#http-get-sample.tab-pane.active
						pre: code 
							| curl http://api.teech.io/users \
							|  -X GET
					div#http-post-sample.tab-pane
						pre: code 
							| curl http://api.teech.io/users \
							|  -X POST \
							|  -H 'Content-Type: application/json' \
							|  -d '{"username":"tim", "password":"Kld98Sld9", "name":"Tim Red"}'
					div#http-put-sample.tab-pane 
						pre: code 
							| curl http://api.teech.io/users \
							|  -X PUT \
							|  -H 'Content-Type: application/json' \
							|  -d '{"fullname":"Tim Roth"}'
					div#http-delete-sample.tab-pane
						pre: code 
							| curl http://api.teech.io/users/8d93iI093jm \
							|  -X DELETE
			a(class="next-step-btn btn btn-primary btn-lg", data-href="#step-7") next <i class="fa fa-chevron-circle-right"></i>
		div.grid-50.walkthrough-example-image.walkthrough-6-step-image
	div#step-7.step.grid-container.set-hidden
		div.grid-50
			h2 Queries
			p Queries let you search through a collection and limit and/or skip the results.
			div.code-sample
				ul.nav.nav-tabs
					li.active: a(data-target="#http-get-sample", data-toggle="tab") GET
				div.tab-content
					div#http-get-sample.tab-pane.active
						pre: code 
							| curl http://api.teech.io/users?query={"username":"tim"} \
							|  -X GET
			a(class="next-step-btn btn btn-primary btn-lg", data-href="#step-8") next <i class="fa fa-chevron-circle-right"></i>
		div.grid-50.walkthrough-example-image.walkthrough-7-step-image
	div#step-8.step.grid-container.set-hidden
		div.grid-50
			h2 Now start building!
			p Awesome, you’re well on your way to building your first application using Teech.io.<br/>Learn more about our platform by heading to our documentation.
			a(href="//teech.io/documentation", class="learn-more-btn btn") <i class="fa fa-list-alt space-right"></i> read the docs
			p Or jump back to the Dashboard to create applications, collections and more.
			a(href="/", class="skip-dashboard btn") <i class="fa fa-home space-right"></i> go to the dashboard
		div.grid-50